data.name: category
data.description: returns products in specified category. By default, all categories are considered.

data.name: group
data.description: Returns products in groups instead of returning all at once.  Accepted values are:  shop: Group products by shop; or cat: Group products by category.  Only the first "group_limit" products are returned for each group. If you want to see more products for some group, you issue another search request with group= left unset and set either shop or category argument.

data.name: group_limit
data.description: Specifies the number of products to be returned in each group. The value must not be larger than group_limit. By default 4 products are returned.

data.name: include_long_desc
data.description: Setting include_long_desc=1 enables long product descriptions. By default, long descriptions are not returned.

data.name: limit
data.description: Limit number of results (either products or groups) returned. The default limit is 40 for a normal search and 8 for a group search.

data.name: offset
data.description: Return results (either products or groups) starting at specified offset. Default offset is 0.

data.name: price_max
data.description: Return only products that cost at most that amount.

data.name: price_min
data.description: Return only products that cost at least that amount.

data.name: q
data.description: A query string with keywords separated by space or + sign. This option is required. A special value q=* can be used to return all of the products in shops.

data.name: random_results
data.description: Include a specified number of random products. Multiple random_results options are allowed. Returns the largest value of products  Example. Request a search with random_results=60&random_results=50%25 (%25 is an escaped % character). The search normally would return 80 products. Since 50% of 80 is 40, which is smaller than 60, an additional 60 random products are included.

data.name: random_seed
data.description: Four char string to be used as random seed. This seed is used when sorting by random or adding random products (window shopping). Queries with the same random_seed will return the same results (unless more products appear in the meantime).

data.name: safe
data.description: Setting safe=-1 enables adult content. By default only safe content will be returned.

data.name: shop
data.description: Only returns products for specified shop. By default, all shops are considered.

data.name: shop_karma_min
data.description: Searches only in shops with at least this karma value.

data.name: sort
data.description: Sort products by specified criteria. Multiple sort= arguments are allowed; the first one takes precedence.  Accepted values are:  match, date, views, sales, random, random_views, price, price_asc, rating, id. : If you request sort=rating&sort=price_asc, products with the highest user rating will be returned first. If there are multiple products with the same rating, price will determine the order they are returned.
A request to this endpoint will search for products by keywords. A request returns a products object, which contains all products found and some associated data.
